speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Captain.

speaker: MAOI MADAKOR
combinedline: Yes, sir?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Tell them we wish to board at once.

speaker: MAOI MADAKOR
combinedline: With all due respect...

speaker: MAOI MADAKOR
combinedline: the ambassadors for the supreme chancellor wish to board immediately.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Yes, of course. As you know, our blockade is perfectly legal...

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: and we'd be happy to receive the ambassadors.

speaker: TC-14
combinedline: I'm TC-14 at your service. This way, please. We are greatly honoured by your visit, Ambassadors. Make yourselves comfortable. My master will be with you shortly.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I have a bad feeling about this.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I don't sense anything.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's not about the mission, Master. It's something elsewhere, elusive.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Don't center on your anxieties, Obi-Wan. Keep your concentration here and now, where it belongs.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: But Master Yoda said I should be mindful of the future.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: But not at the expense of the moment. Be mindful of the living Force, young Padawan.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, Master. How do you think this trade viceroy will deal with the chancellor's demands?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: These Federation types are cowards. The negotiations will be short.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: What? What did you say?

speaker: TC-14
combinedline: The ambassadors are Jedi knights, I believe.

speaker: DAULTAY
combinedline: I knew it. They're here to force a settlement.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Distract them. I will contact Lord Sidious.

speaker: DAULTAY
combinedline: Are you brain-dead? I'm not going in there with two Jedi.

speaker: DAULTAY
combinedline: Send a droid.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Is it in their nature to make us wait this long?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: No. I sense an unusual amount of fear... for something as trivial as this trade dispute.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: What is it?

speaker: DAULTAY
combinedline: This scheme of yours has failed, Lord Sidious. The blockade is finished. We dare not go against these Jedi.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Viceroy, I don't want this stunted slime in my sight again.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: This turn of events is unfortunate. We must accelerate our plans. Begin landing your troops.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: My lord, is that legal?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I will make it legal.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: And the Jedi?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: The chancellor should never have brought them into this. Kill them immediately.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Yes, Yes, my lord. As you wish.

speaker: ANTIDAR WILLIAMS
combinedline: Captain, look!

speaker: MAOI MADAKOR
combinedline: Shields...

speaker: TC-14
combinedline: Sorry.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Dioxis.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: They must be dead by now. Destroy what's left of them.

speaker: TC-14
combinedline: Oh! Excuse me.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Check it out, Corporal. We'll cover you.

speaker: BATTLE DROID 2
combinedline: Roger, roger.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Uh-oh. Blast them.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: What is going on down there?

speaker: TEY HOW
combinedline: We lost the transmission, sir.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: Have you ever encountered a Jedi knight before, sir?

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Well, no, but I don't...

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Seal off the bridge.

speaker: TEY HOW
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: That won't be enough, sir.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: I want droidekas

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: up here at once!

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: We will not survive this.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Close the blast doors!

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: That will hold them.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: They are still coming through.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: This is impossible!

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: Where are those droidekas?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Master! Destroyers! They have shield generators!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: It's a standoff. Let's go.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: They're no match for droidekas.

speaker: TEY HOW
combinedline: Sir! They've gone up the ventilation shaft.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Battle droids.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's an invasion army.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: This is an odd play for the Trade Federation. We've got to warn the Naboo and contact Chancellor Valorum. Let's split up. Stow aboard separate ships and meet down on the planet.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You were right about one thing, Master. The negotiations were short.

speaker: TEY HOW
combinedline: Sir, a transmission from the planet.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: It's Queen Amidala herself.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: At last we are getting results.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Again you come before us, Your Highness.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You will not be so pleased when you hear what I have to say, Viceroy. Your trade boycott of our planet has ended.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: I was not aware of such failure.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I have word that the chancellor's ambassadors are with you now... and that you have been commanded to reach settlement.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: I know nothing of any ambassadors. You must be mistaken.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Beware, Viceroy. The Federation has gone too far this time.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: We would never do anything without the approval of the senate. You assume too much.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We will see.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: She's right. The senate will never...

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: It's too late now.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: Do you think she suspects an attack?

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: I don't know. But we must move quickly to disrupt all communications down there.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Negotiations haven't started because the ambassadors aren't there? How could that be true? I have assurances from the chancellor his ambassadors did arrive.

speaker: [DISTORTED VOICE]
combinedline: It must... handiwork... negotiate... ambassadors... - nobody would...

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Senator Palpatine. What's happening?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Check the transmission generator.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: A communications disruption can mean only one thing: Invasion.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: The Federation would not dare go that far.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: The senate would revoke their trade franchise, and they'd be finished.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We must continue to rely on negotiation.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: Negotiation? We've lost all communications.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: And where are the chancellor's ambassadors?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: This is a dangerous situation, Your Highness. Our security volunteers will be no match... against a battle-hardened Federation army.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I will not condone a course of action that will lead us to war.

speaker: OOM-9
combinedline: Yes, Viceroy?

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: Captain, we've searched the ship... and there is no trace of the Jedi. They may have gotten on one of your landing craft.

speaker: OOM-9
combinedline: If they're down here, sir, we'll fnd them.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Use caution. These Jedi are not to be underestimated.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, no!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Get away! Get out of here! Get down!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Was'n dat? Hey, wait! Oh, mooie-mooie, I love you.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You almost got us killed. Are you brainless?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: I spake.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: The ability to speak does not make you intelligent. Now, get out of here.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: No, no, mesa stay. Mesa culled Jar Jar Binks. Mesa your humble servant.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: That won't be necessary.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, but it 'tis. Tis demanded by the gods, it 'tis. Oh, no!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Stay down!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: You saved my again.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What's this?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: A local. Let's get out of here before more droids show up.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: More? More did you spake?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Ex-squeeze-me, but de mostest safest place would be Gunga City. Is where I grew up. Tis a hidden city.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: A city?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Uh-huh.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Can you take us there?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: On second thought, no. Not really, no.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: No?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Tis embarrassing... but my afraid my've been banished. My forgotten. Da bosses would do terrible tings to me. Terrible tings to me if me goen back dare.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You hear that?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Yah.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: That is the sound of a thousand terrible things heading this way.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: If they find us, they will crush us... grind us into tiny pieces and blast us into oblivion.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh. Yousa point is well seen.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Dis way. Hurry!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: How much further?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Wesa goen underwater, okeyday? Ah, my warning you. Gungans no liken outsiders, so don't spect a warm welcome.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Don't worry. This hasn't been our day for warm welcomes.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Yousa follow me now, okeyday? So good bein home!

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Hey, yousa. Stopa dare.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Heyo-dales, Cap'n Tarpals. Mesa back.

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Noah gain, Jar Jar. Yousa goen tada bosses. Yousa in big dudu dis time.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: How wude.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Yousa cannot bees hair. Dis army of Mackineeks up dare is new weesong.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: A droid army is about to attack the Naboo. We must warn them.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Wesa no like da Naboo. Da Naboo tink day so smarty. Day tink day brains so big.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Once those droids take control of the surface, they will take control of you.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Mesa no tink so. Day not know of uss-en.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You and the Naboo form a symbiont circle. What happens to one of you will affect the other. You must understand this.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Wesa no carrrre-nn about da Naboo.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Then speed us on our way.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Wesa ganna speed yous away.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We could use a transport.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Wesa give yousa una bongo. Da speediest way tooda Naboo... tis goen through the planet core. Now... go.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Thank you for your help. We leave in peace.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Master, what's a bongo?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: A transport, I hope.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Deysa setten yousa up. Goen through da planet core? Bad bombin'. Any help here would be hot.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Master, we're short on time.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We'll need a navigator to get us through the planet's core. This Gungan may be of help.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: What is to become of Jar Jar Binks here?

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Hisen to be pune-ished.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I saved his life. He owes me what you call a "life-debt." Your gods demand that his life belongs to me now.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Binks... yousa havena liveplay with thisen hisen?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: MM HMM

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Begone wit him!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Count me outta dis one. Better dead here than dead in da core.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Yee gods! What mesa sayin?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Dis is nutsen.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, gooberfish!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Why were you banished, Jar Jar?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: It's a longo tale-o... buta a small part of it would be mesa... clumsy.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You were banished for being clumsy?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Yousa might'n be sayin dat. Mesa caused mabee one two-y lettle bitty axadentes, huh? Yud-say boom da gasser... den crashin der boss's heyblibber, den banished.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Uh oh! Big gooberfish! Huge-o teeth!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: There's always a bigger fish.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa tink we goen back now.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: The invasion is on schedule, my lord.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I have the senate bogged down in procedures. They will have no choice but to accept your control of the system.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: The queen has great faith that the senate will side with her.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Queen Amidala is young and naive. You will find controlling her will not be difficult.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Yes, my lord.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: You didn't tell him about the missing Jedi.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: No need to report that to him until we have something to report.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Where wesa goin?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Don't worry. The Force will guide us.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, maxi big, da Force. Well, dat smells stinkowiff.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We're losing power.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, no!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Wesa dyin' here.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Just relax. We're not in trouble yet.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: What "yet"? Monsters out dare. Leak'n in here. All sink'n and no power? Whena yousa tinkin wesa in trouble?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Power's back.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Monster's back!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Relax.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You overdid it.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Horrible.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Head for that outcropping.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, boy.

speaker: OOM-9
combinedline: Viceroy, we have captured the queen.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Ah, victory.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Dis'n loverly.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: How will you explain this invasion to the senate?

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: The queen and I will sign a treaty that will legitimize our occupation here. I have assurances it will be ratifed by the senate.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: I will not cooperate.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Now, now, Your Highness. In time, your people's suffering will persuade you to see our point of view.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Commander.

speaker: BATTLE DROID COMMANDER
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Process them.

speaker: BATTLE DROID COMMANDER
combinedline: Captain, take them to Camp 4.

speaker: BATTLE DROID CAPTAIN
combinedline: Roger, roger.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Whoops

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We should leave the street, Your Highness.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Get their weapons.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Yousa guys bombad!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We're ambassadors for the supreme chancellor.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: Your negotiations seemed to have failed, Ambassador.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: The negotiations never took place. It's urgent that we make contact with the Republic.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: They've knocked out all our communications.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Do you have transports?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: In the main hangar. This way. There are too many of them.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: That won't be a problem. Your Highness, under the circumstances, I suggest you come to Coruscant with us.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Thank you, Ambassador, but my place is with my people.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: They will kill you if you stay.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: They wouldn't dare.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: They need her to sign a treaty to make this invasion legal. They can't afford to kill her.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: There is something else behind all this, Your Highness. There's no logic in the Federation's move here. My feelings tell me they will destroy you.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: Our only hope is for the senate to side with us. Senator Palpatine will need your help.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Either choice presents great danger... to us all.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We are brave, Your Highness.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: If you are to leave, Your Highness, it must be now.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Then I will plead our case to the senate.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Be careful, Governor.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: We'll need to free those pilots.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'll deal with that.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Halt.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I'm ambassador to the supreme chancellor. I'm taking these people to Coruscant.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Where are you taking them?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: To Coruscant.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Coruscant? Uh, that doesn't compute. Uh, wait. Uh, you're under arrest.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Come on. Move!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Go!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Now, stay here and keep out of trouble.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Hello, boyos.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: There's the blockade. The shield generator's been hit!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: How wude!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We're losing droids fast.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: If we can't get the shield generator fxed, we'll be sitting ducks.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: The shields are gone.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: The power's back!

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: That little droid did it. He bypassed the main power drive. Deflector shields up at maximum.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: There's not enough power to get us to Coruscant. The hyperdrive is leaking.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We'll have to land somewhere to refuel and repair the ship.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Here, Master. Tatooine. It's small, out of the way, poor. The Trade Federation have no presence there.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: How can you be sure?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: It's controlled by the Hutts.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: You can't take Her Royal Highness there. The Hutts are gangsters. If they discovered her...

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: It'd be no different than if we landed on a system controlled by the Federation... except that the Hutts aren't looking for her... which gives us the advantage.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: And Queen Amidala, has she signed the treaty?

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: She has disappeared, my lord. One Naboo cruiser got past the blockade.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I want that treaty signed.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: My lord... it's impossible to locate the ship. It's out of our range.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Not for a Sith. This is my apprentice... Darth Maul. He will find your lost ship.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: This is getting out of hand. Now there are two of them.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: We should not have made this bargain.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: An extremely well-put-together little droid, Your Highness. Without a doubt, it saved the ship, as well as our lives.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: It is to be commended. What is its number?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: R2D2, Your Highness.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Thank you,R2D2.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Padme. Clean this droid up as best you can. It deserves our gratitude.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Continue, Captain.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Your Highness, with your permission... we're heading for a remote planet called Tatooine. It's in a system far beyond the reach of the Trade Federation.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: I do not agree with the Jedi on this.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You must trust my judgment, Your Highness.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Hello. Sorry. Husa are yousa?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'm Padme

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa Jar Jar Binks.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You're a Gungan, aren't you? How'd you end up here with us?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: My no know. Mesa day starten pitty okeyday witda brisky morning munchen. Den boom! Getten berry scared... and grabben dat Jedi, and pow... mesa here.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa getten berry, berry scared.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: That's it... Tatooine.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: There's a settlement.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Land near the outskirts. We don't want to attract attention.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The hyperdrive generator's gone, Master. We'll need a new one.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: That'll complicate things. Be wary. I sense a disturbance in the Force.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I feel it also, Master.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Don't let them send any transmissions.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: The sun doen murder to mesa skin.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Wait!

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Wait.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Her Highness commands you to take her handmaiden with you.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: No more commands from Her Highness today, Captain. The spaceport is not going to be pleasant.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: The queen wishes it. She's curious about the planet.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: This is not a good idea.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Stay close to me.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Moisture farms, for the most part. Some indigenous tribes and scavengers. The few spaceports like this one... are havens for those that don't wish to be found.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Like us.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Dissen berry, berry bad.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Icky, icky goo!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We'll try one of the smaller dealers.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Good day to you. What do you want?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I need parts for a J-type 327 Nubian.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Ah, yes! Nubian. We have lots of that.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Boy, get in here now!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: My droid has a readout of what I need.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: What took you so long?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I was cleaning the fan switches.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Watch the store. I've got some selling to do.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: So, let me take thee out back, huh? We'll find what you need.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Don't touch anything.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Are you an angel?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: An angel. I heard the deep space pilots talk about them. They're the most beautiful creatures in the universe. They live on the moons of lego,

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I think.

combinedline: We owe you everything, Ani.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: It's so wonderful, Ani. You have brought hope to those who have none. I'm so very proud of you.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: You! You swindled me. You knew the boy was going to win. Somehow you knew it. I lost everything.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Whenever you gamble, my friend, eventually you lose. Bring the parts to the main hangar. I'll come by your shop later on so you can release the boy.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: You can't have him. It wasn't a fair bet.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Would you like to discuss it with the Hutts? I'm sure they can settle this.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Take him.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Hidoe!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, we have all the essential parts we need.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I'm going back. Some unfinished business. I won't be long.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Why do I sense we've picked up another pathetic life-form?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: It's the boy who's responsible for getting us these parts. Get this hyperdrive generator installed.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, Master. That shouldn't take long.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Come on. Hup!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Hey. These are yours.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Mom, we sold the pod! Look at all the money we have!

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: My goodness! But that's so wonderful, Ani.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: And he has been freed.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You're no longer a slave.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Did you hear that?

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Now you can make your dreams come true, Ani. You are free.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Will you take him with you? Is he to become a Jedi?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Yes. Our meeting was not a coincidence. Nothing happens by accident.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You mean I get to come with you in your starship?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Anakin... training to become a Jedi is not an easy challenge... and even if you succeed, it's a hard life.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: But I wanna go. It's what I've always dreamed of doing.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Can I go, Mom?

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Anakin... this path has been placed before you. The choice is yours alone.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I wanna do it.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Then pack your things. We haven't much time.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yippee!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What about Mom? Is she free too?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I tried to free your mother, Ani, but Watto wouldn't have it.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're coming with us, aren't you, Mom?

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Son, my place is here. My future is here. It is time for you to let go.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't want things to change.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: But you can't stop the change... any more than you can stop the suns from setting. I love you. Now hurry.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Thank you.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I'll watch after him. You have my word. Will you be all right?

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Yeah.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, Oh my. Oh! Hello, Master Anakin.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, 3PO, I've been freed... and I'm going away in a starship.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Master Anakin, you are my maker and I wish you well. However, I should prefer it if I were a little more completed.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm sorry I wasn't able to finish you, 3PO... give you coverings and all. I'm gonna miss working on you. You've been a great pal. I'll make sure Mom doesn't sell you or anything.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Sell me?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Bye.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, my.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I can't do it, Mom. I just can't do it.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Ani...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Will I ever see you again?

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: What does your heart tell you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I hope so. Yes. I guess.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Then we will see each other again.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I will come back and free you, Mom. I promise.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Now, be brave... and don't look back. Don't look back.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Qui-Gon, sir, wait! I'm tired!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Anakin! Drop! Go! Tell them to take off!

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Qui-Gon's in trouble.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Take off. Over there. Fly low.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Are you all right?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I think so.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What was it?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I'm not sure... but it was well-trained in the Jedi arts.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: BEEPS TWICE

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: My guess is it was after the queen.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What are we gonna do about it?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We shall be patient.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Anakin Skywalker... meet Obi-Wan Kenobi.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Hi! You're a Jedi too? Pleased to meet you.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Your queen is lost, your people are starving... and you, Governor, are going to die... much sooner than your people, I'm afraid.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: This invasion will gain you nothing. We're a democracy. The people have decided.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Take him away.

speaker: OOM-9
combinedline: My troops are in position to begin searching the swamps... for these rumoured underwater villages. They will not stay hidden for long.

speaker: BIBBLE
combinedline: The death toll is catastrophic. We must bow to their wishes. You must contact me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You all right?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It's very cold.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You come from a warm planet, Ani. A little too warm for my taste. Space is cold.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You seem sad.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: The queen is worried. Her people are suffering, dying. She must convince the senate to intervene or... I'm not sure what'll happen.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I made this for you... so you'd remember me. I carved it out of a japor snippet. It'll bring you good fortune.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: It's beautiful. But I don't need this to remember you by. Many things will change when we reach the capital, Ani... but my caring for you will remain.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I care for you, too, only l...

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Miss your mother.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: Coruscant. The entire planet is one big city. There's Chancellor Valorum's shuttle. And look over there. Senator Palpatine is waiting for us.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It is a great gift to see you alive, Your Majesty. With the communications breakdown, we've been very concerned. I'm anxious to hear your report on the situation. May I present Supreme Chancellor Valorum.

speaker: VALORUM
combinedline: Welcome, Your Highness. It's an honour to fnally meet you in person.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Thank you, Supreme Chancellor.

speaker: VALORUM
combinedline: I must relay to you how distressed everyone is over the current situation. I've called for a special session of the senate to hear your position.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: I'm grateful for your concern, Chancellor.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: There is a question of procedure... but I'm confdent we can overcome it.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I must speak with the Jedi Council immediately. The situation has become much more complicated.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ani, come on.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Da queen's a bein grossly nice, mesa tinks. Pitty hot.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: There is no civility, only politics. The Republic is not what it once was. The senate is full of greedy, squabbling delegates. There is no interest in the common good. I must be frank, Your Majesty. There is little chance the senate will act on the invasion.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Chancellor Valorum seems to think there is hope. If I may say so, Your Majesty... the chancellor has little real power. He is mired by baseless accusations of corruption. The bureaucrats are in charge now. What options have we?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Our best choice would be to push for the election... of a stronger supreme chancellor... one who could control the bureaucrats... and give us justice. You could call for a vote of no confidence in Chancellor Valorum.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He has been our strongest supporter.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Our only other choice would be to submit a plea to the courts.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: The courts take even longer to decide things than the senate. Our people are dying, Senator. We must do something quickly to stop the Federation.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: To be realistic, Your Majesty... I think we're going to have to accept Federation control... for the time being.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: That is something I cannot do.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: He was trained in the Jedi arts. My only conclusion can be that it was a Sith lord.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: Impossible. The Sith have been extinct for a millennium.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I do not believe the Sith could have returned without us knowing.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Hard to see, the dark side is.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: We will use all our resources to unravel this mystery. We will discover the identity of your attacker. May the Force be with you.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Master Qui-Gon. More to say have you?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: With your permission, my master... I have encountered a vergence in the Force.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: A vergence, you say.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Located around a person?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: A boy. His cells have the highest concentration of midi-chlorians... I have seen in a life-form. It is possible he was conceived by the midi-chlorians.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: You refer to the prophecy of the one who will bring balance to the Force. You believe it's this boy?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I don't presume to...

speaker: YODA
combinedline: But you do. Revealed your opinion is.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I request the boy be tested, Master.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Oh? Trained as a Jedi you request for him, hmm?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Finding him was the will of the Force. I have no doubt of that.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Bring him before us, then.

speaker: GUARD
combinedline: The boy's here to see Padme.

speaker: HANDMAIDEN
combinedline: Let him in.

speaker: HANDMAIDEN
combinedline: I'm sorry, Ani, but Padme's not here right now.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Who is it?

speaker: HANDMAIDEN
combinedline: Anakin Skywalker to see Padme, Your Highness.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I've sent Padme on an errand.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm on my way to the Jedi temple... to start my training, I hope. I may never see her again, so I came to say goodbye.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We will tell her for you. We are sure her heart goes with you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Thank you, Your Highness.

speaker: VALORUM
combinedline: The chair recognizes the senator from the sovereign system of Naboo.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Supreme Chancellor, delegates of the senate... a tragedy has occurred... which started right here with the taxation of trade routes... and has now engulfed our entire planet... in the oppression of the Trade Federation.

speaker: LOTT DOD
combinedline: This is outrageous! I object to the senator's statements.

speaker: VALORUM
combinedline: The chair does not recognize the senator from the Trade Federation at this time.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: To state our allegations, I present Queen Amidala... recently elected ruler of the Naboo... who speaks on our behalf.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Honourable representatives of the Republic... I come to you under the gravest of circumstances. The Naboo system has been invaded by the droid armies of the Trade...

speaker: LOTT DOD
combinedline: I object! There is no proof! This is incredible. We recommend a commission be sent to Naboo to ascertain the truth.

speaker: AKS MOE
combinedline: The Congress of Malastare... concurs with the honourable delegate from the Trade Federation. A commission must be appointed.

speaker: VALORUM
combinedline: The point...

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Excuse me, Chancellor.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Enter the bureaucrat. The true rulers of the Republic. And on the payroll of the Trade Federation, I might add. This is where Chancellor Valorum's strength will disappear.

speaker: VALORUM
combinedline: The point is conceded. Will you defer your motion to allow a commission... to explore the validity of your accusations?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I will not defer. I've come before you to resolve this attack on our sovereignty now. I was not elected to watch my people suffer and die... while you discuss this invasion in a committee. If this body is not capable of action... I suggest new leadership is needed. I move for a vote of no confdence... in Chancellor Valorum's leadership.

speaker: SENATORS
combinedline: Vote now! Vote now!

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Order!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Now they will elect a new chancellor... a strong chancellor... one who will not let our tragedy continue.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The boy will not pass the council's test, Master. He's too old.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Anakin will become a Jedi, I promise you.

speaker: OB-WAN
combinedline: Do not defy the council, Master, not again.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I shall do what I must, Obi-Wan.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: If you would just follow the code, you would be on the council. They will not go along with you this time.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You still have much to learn, my young apprentice.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: A ship. A cup. A ship. A speeder.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: How feel you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Cold, sir.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Afraid are you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No, sir.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: See through you we can.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Be mindful of your feelings.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: Your thoughts dwell on your mother.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I miss her.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Afraid to lose her, I think, mmm?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What has that got to do with anything?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Everything. Fear is the path to the dark side. Fear leads to anger. Anger leads to hate. Hate leads to suffering. I sense much fear in you.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Yousa tinking yousa people ganna die?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't know.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Gungans get pasted too, eh?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I hope not.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Gungans no die'n without a fght. Wesa warriors. Wesa got a grand army. Dat's why you no liken us, mesa tinks.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Your Highness? Your Highness... Senator Palpatine has been nominated to succeed Valorum... as supreme chancellor.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: A surprise, to be sure, but a welcome one. Your Majesty, if I am elected, I promise to put an end to corruption.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Who else has been nominated?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Bail Antilles of Alderaan and Ainlee Teem of Malastare.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I feel confident our situation will create a strong sympathy vote for us. I will be chancellor.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I fear by the time you have control of the bureaucrats, Senator... there'll be nothing left of our people, our way of life.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I understand your concern, Your Majesty. Unfortunately, the Federation has possession of our planet.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Senator, this is your arena. I feel I must return to mine. I've decided to go back to Naboo.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Go back? But, Your Majesty, be realistic. They'll force you to sign the treaty.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I will sign no treaty, Senator. My fate will be no different than that of our people.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Captain.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Your Highness.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ready my ship.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Please, Your Majesty. Stay here where it's safe.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: It is clear to me now that the Republic no longer functions. I pray you will bring sanity and compassion back to the senate.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: The Force is strong with him.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: He is to be trained, then?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: No, he will not be trained.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: No?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: He is too old.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: He is the chosen one. You must see it.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Clouded this boy's future is.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I will train him, then. I take Anakin as my Padawan learner.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: An apprentice you have, Qui-Gon. Impossible to take on a second.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: The code forbids it.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Obi-Wan is ready.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I am ready to face the trials.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Our own counsel we will keep on who is ready.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: He is headstrong and he has much to learn of the living Force... but he is capable. There is little more he can learn from me.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Young Skywalker's fate will be decided later.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Now is not the time for this. The senate is voting for a new supreme chancellor... and Queen Amidala is returning home... which will put pressure on the Federation and could widen the confrontation.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: And draw out the queen's attacker.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Go with the queen to Naboo and discover the identity of this dark warrior. This is the clue we need... to unravel the mystery of the Sith.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: May the Force be with you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's not disrespect, Master. It's the truth.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: From your point of view.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The boy is dangerous. They all sense it. Why can't you?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: His fate is uncertain. He's not dangerous. The council will decide Anakin's future. That should be enough for you. Now get on board.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Qui-Gon, sir, I don't want to be a problem.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You won't be, Ani. I'm not allowed to train you... so I want you to watch me and be mindful. Always remember: Your focus determines your reality. Stay close to me and you'll be safe.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master, sir... I heard Yoda talking about midi-chlorians. I've been wondering... What are midi-chlorians?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Midi-chlorians are a microscopic life-form... that resides within all living cells.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: They live inside me?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Inside your cells, yes. And we are symbionts with them.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Symbionts?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Life-forms living together for mutual advantage. Without the midi-chlorians, life could not exist... and we would have no knowledge of the Force. They continually speak to us... telling us the will of the Force. When you learn to quiet your mind... you'll hear them speaking to you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't understand.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: With time and training, Ani, you will. You will.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Your Majesty, it is our pleasure to continue to serve and protect you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I welcome your help. Senator Palpatine fears that the Federation means to destroy me.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I assure you I will not allow that to happen.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Wesa goin' home!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Come on, Artoo.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Is the planet secure?

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: We have taken over the last pockets of primitive life-forms. We are in complete control of the planet now.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Good. I will see to it that in the senate... things stay as they are. I am sending my apprentice, Darth Maul, to join you.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Yes, my lord.

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: A Sith here?

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: Those are the forward stabilizers.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: And those two control the pitch?

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: You catch on pretty quick.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: As soon as we land... the Federation will arrest you and force you to sign the treaty.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: I agree. I'm not sure what you wish to accomplish by this.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I will take back what's ours.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: There are too few of us, Your Highness. We have no army.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: And I can only protect you. I can't fight a war for you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Jar Jar Binks.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa, Your Highness?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Yes. I need your help.

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: I have one battleship on my scope.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's a droid control ship.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: They've probably spotted us.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We haven't much time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Jar Jar is on his way to the Gungan city, Master.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Good.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Do you think the queen's idea will work?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: The Gungans will not be easily swayed. And we cannot use our power to help her.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'm sorry for my behaviour, Master. It's not my place to disagree with you about the boy. And I am grateful you think I'm ready to take the trials.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: You've been a good apprentice, Obi-Wan. And you're a much wiser man than I am. I foresee you will become a great Jedi knight.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Desa nobody dare! The Gungan city is deserted! Some kinda fight, mesa tinks.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Do you think they have been taken to the camps?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: More likely they were wiped out.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa no tink so.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Do you know where they are, Jar Jar?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: When in trouble, Gungans go to sacred place. Mesa show you. Come on. Mesa show you!

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Your Honour, Queen Amidala of the Naboo.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Heyo dadee Big Boss Nass, Your Honour.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Jar Jar Binks. Who's da uss-en uthers?

speaker: SABE
combinedline: I am Queen Amidala of the Naboo. I come before you in peace.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Ah, Naboo biggen. Yousa bringen da Mackineeks. Yousa all bombad.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: We have searched you out because we wish to form an alliance.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Your Honour.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Whosa dis?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I am Queen Amidala. This is my decoy... my protection, my loyal bodyguard. I'm sorry for my deception, but it was necessary to protect myself. Although we do not always agree, Your Honour... our two great societies have always lived in peace. The Trade Federation has destroyed all that we have worked so hard to build. If we do not act quickly, all will be lost forever. I ask you to help us. No, I beg you to help us. We are your humble servants. Our fate is in your hands.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Yousa no tinken yousa greater den da Gungans? Mesa lika dis! Maybe... wesa... being friends.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: We've sent our patrols. We already located their starship in the swamp.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It won't be long, my lord. This is an unexpected move for her. It's too aggressive.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Lord Maul, be mindful. Let them make the first move.

speaker: DARTH MAUL
combinedline: Yes, my master.

speaker: GUNGAN GUARD
combinedline: Deysa comin!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: All right!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: They're here!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Good. They made it.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Yousa doen grand. Jar Jar bring uss-en and da Naboo together.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Oh, no, no, no.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: So, wesa make you... bombad general.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: General?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Captain.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Your Highness.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What is the situation?

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Almost everyone's in camps. A few hundred police and guards formed an underground resistance movement. I brought back as many of the leaders as I could. The Federation army's also much larger than we thought... and much stronger. Your Highness, this is a battle I do not think that we can win.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: The battle is a diversion. The Gungans must draw the droid army away from the cities.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Artoo.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We can enter the city using the secret passages on the waterfall side. Once we get to the main entrance... Captain Panaka will create a diversion. Then we can enter the palace and capture the viceroy. Without the viceroy, they will be lost and confused.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What do you think, Master Jedi?

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: The viceroy will be well-guarded.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: The diffculty is getting into the throne room. Once we're inside, we shouldn't have a problem.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: There is a possibility, with this diversion, many Gungans will be killed.

speaker: BOSS NASS
combinedline: Wesa ready to do our-san part. We have a plan which should immobilize the droid army. We will send what pilots we have... to knock out the droid control ship orbiting the planet.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: A well-conceived plan. However, there's great risk. The weapons on your fghters may not penetrate the shields.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: And there's an even bigger danger. If the viceroy escapes, Your Highness... he will return with another droid army.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Well, that is why we must not fail to get the viceroy. Everything depends on it.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: She is more foolish than I thought.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: We are sending all troops... to meet this army assembling near the swamp. It appears to be made up of primitives.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: This will work to our advantage.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: I have your approval to proceed, then, my lord?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Wipe them out. All of them.

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Halt! Starting up the shield.

speaker: OOM-9
combinedline: Open fire.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Once we get inside, you find a safe place to hide and stay there.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sure.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Stay there.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Roger, roger.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: I thought the battle was going to take place far from here. This is too close.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Ani, find cover. Quick!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Get to your ships!

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: Fighters straight ahead.

speaker: WENDIK
combinedline: Roger, Bravo Leader.

speaker: ELLBERGER
combinedline: Roger, Bravo Leader.

speaker: OOM-9
combinedline: Cease fre.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Steady. Steady.

speaker: DAULTY DOFINE
combinedline: Activate the droids.

speaker: TEY HOW
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Ouch time.

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Fire!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: My guess is the viceroy's in the throne room.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Red group! Blue group! Everybody, this way!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Hey, wait for me!

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Anakin, stay where you are. You'll be safe there.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: But l...

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Stay in that cockpit.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: We'll handle this.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We'll take the long way.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We gotta do something, Artoo.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm trying to! I don't know where the trigger is!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Oops, wrong one. Maybe it's this one. Nope. Wait. Here it is. Yeah!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Let's go!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It's on automatic pilot.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Try to override it.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We don't have time for this, Captain.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Look, there they are. That's where the autopilot's taking us.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Dumb droid. Take that! Get off! Get off! Get off! Get off!

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: The deflector shield is too strong.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: This is tense! Artoo, get us off this autopilot. It's gonna get us both killed.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You did it, Artoo! Let's go left.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Go back? Qui-Gon told me to stay in this cockpit, so that's what I'm gonna do. I'll try spinning. That's a good trick.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I know we're in trouble. Just hang on.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Go! Ascension guns!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Retreat! Retreat! Dis is nutsen. Uh-oh. Big boomers. Uh-oh! Hey! Hey! Give me a lift!

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Jar Jar, usen da booma!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: What? Mesa no have a booma!

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: Here. Taken dis one. Jar Jar! Jump, Jar Jar, jump!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Put down your weapons. They win this round.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: SHRIEK

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We're hit, Artoo!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm trying to stop! I'm trying to stop!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Everything's overheated.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Oops. This is not good.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: NOOOOOOOOOOOOO

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: No giben up, General Jar Jar. Mesa think of something.

speaker: 3B3-888
combinedline: Hands up.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: My give up. My give up.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Your little insurrection is at an end, Your Highness. Time for you to sign the treaty and end... this pointless debate in the senate.

speaker: SABE
combinedline: Viceroy! Your occupation here has ended. After her. This one's a decoy.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Captain!

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: Jam the doors.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Now, Viceroy, we will discuss a new treaty.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: BEEPS THREE TIMES

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes! We have power.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Shields up. Take this! And this! Whoa! Oops.

speaker: TEY HOW
combinedline: We're losing power. There seems to be a problem with the main reactor.

speaker: DAULTY DOFINE
combinedline: Impossible! Nothing can get through our shield.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Let's get outta here.

speaker: ELLBERGER
combinedline: What's that? It's blowing up from the inside!

speaker: RIC OLIE
combinedline: We didn't hit it.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Now, this is Podracing.

speaker: WENDIK
combinedline: Look, one of ours, out of the main hold!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Whooo! Whooo!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: What the... Was'n they doing?

speaker: CAPT. TARPALS
combinedline: The control ship has been destroyed. Look!

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: They all broke-ed.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: No, it's too late.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No.

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Obi-Wan. Promise... Promise me you will train the boy.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, Master. He is the chosen one. He will bring balance. Train him.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Now, Viceroy... you're going to have to go back to the senate and explain all this.

speaker: CAPT. PANAKA
combinedline: I think you can kiss your trade franchise goodbye.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: We are indebted to you for your bravery, Obi-Wan Kenobi.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: And you, young Skywalker. We will watch your career with great interest.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Congratulations on your election, Chancellor.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Your boldness has saved our people, Your Majesty. It's you who should be congratulated. Together we shall bring peace and prosperity to the Republic.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Confer on you the level of Jedi knight the council does. But agree with your taking this boy as your Padawan learner... I do not.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Qui-Gon believed in him.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: The chosen one the boy may be. Nevertheless... grave danger I fear in his training.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Master Yoda, I gave Qui-Gon my word. I will train Anakin. Without the approval of the council, if I must.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Qui-Gon's defance I sense in you. Need that you do not. Agree with you the council does. Your apprentice Skywalker will be.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: MOANS TWICE

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What will happen to me now?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The council have granted me permission to train you. You will be a Jedi, I promise.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: There's no doubt the mysterious warrior was a Sith.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Always two there are. No more, no less. A master and an apprentice.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: But which was destroyed? The master or the apprentice?

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Hello, everybody!

speaker: BOSS NASS
